===Talking to Asgarnia Smith===
* '''Player:''' Hey, I know you! You're that archaeologist! What was your name again...?
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' You don't remember my name?! You don't remember the world famous Asgarnia Smith, archaeologist extraordinaire?
* '''Player:''' No... sorry. It's not a very memorable name.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' All that work we did together, and you don't even remember my name.
* '''Player:''' To be fair, we never really did that much work together. You sent me on a treasure hunt, but you never really contributed much yourself.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' And a good job I didn't! I never saw a single ounce of gold from that partnership.
* '''Player:''' Well if a partnership with me was so disappointing, how come you're here?
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Bah, I'm not here for you, kid. I'm here for treasure!
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' After our last escapade turned out to be pointless, I set out in search of a new adventure! I started off on Karamja, but that didn't really go anywhere...
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' In the end, I came back to the desert and dug up this place! I've spent ages trying to work out how to get in, only for you to walk up and open the door right away!
* '''Player:''' Yeah... funny that. They opened for me because of some magical abilities I gained on our last treasure hunt. You know, that one you were saying was pointless.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Huh... Well, who'd have thought...
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Alright then, kid, I'll tell you what... You didn't find us any proper treasure last time around, so now's your chance to redeem yourself!
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' I'm sure this place is the key to finding riches beyond imagination, and I, Asgarnia Smith, am willing to enter into a partnership with you, er...
* '''Player:''' You don't remember my name either, do you? It's [player name].
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Yes, as I was saying, I, Asgarnia Smith, am willing to enter into a partnership with you, [player name], to uncover those riches!
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Who knows, perhaps you'll even learn a thing or two from a master treasure hun- I mean, a master archaeologist like me.
* '''Player:''' ...
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' And I am willing to offer you an exclusive rate of a forty percent split!
* '''Player:''' Fifty percent.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Absolutely! A forty-five percent split! So, kid, what do you say?
* '''Player:''' How about I look around while I think about it?
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Of course!
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Asgarnia Smith again====
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Well, kid, any thoughts on my offer?
* '''Player:''' I'm still looking around. I'll decide once I know a bit more about what this place is.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Of course! Take as much time as you need, as long as you don't take long.
* '''Player:''' Right...
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Asgarnia Smith after inspecting the vault===
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Well, kid, any thoughts on my offer?
* '''Player:''' Do you not want to hear about what I've found first?
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Oh, yes, go ahead!
* '''Player:''' According to that plaque over there, this place is a vault that was built to protect the 'mighty treasures' of the 'Empty Lord' from 'the soulless betrayers'.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Mighty treasures, you say? Fantastic! Any idea how to access them?
* '''Player:''' I'm guessing it has something to do with these statues. It looks like each of them is meant to be holding something.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Ah, so we need to find whatever it is they should be holding. Classic treasure vault puzzle! Where do you plan to start?
* '''Player:''' Well hang on there. I haven't actually agreed to anything yet.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' But surely you can't turn down an opportunity like this! You said it yourself: Mighty treasures!
* '''Player:''' Mighty treasures that we can't access.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Now look here, kid. You won't get far in life with an attitude like that. Is there really nothing else we have to go on?
* '''Player:''' We have four names: Vardorvis, Perseriya, Duke Sucellus and the Whisperer.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' They sound like pretty solid leads to me. If we can find these four individuals, maybe we can also find whatever it is we need to get to the treasure.
* '''Player:''' That's a big 'if' right there. This vault is clearly Zarosian, which means whoever these four are, they're from thousands of years ago. They're probably all long- dead now.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Zarosian? I'm sure I've heard that term before...
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Ah yes! Those recent discoveries at the Digsite! I bet my good friend Terry Balando can help. Why don't you talk to him?
* '''Player:''' Again, I've not actually agreed to help.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' No, but you're going to. I can tell. The thrill of the adventure is too much to resist. Not to mention that thirty percent split!
* '''Player:''' Fifty percent.
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' So we're agreed? Excellent! You'll find Terry at the Digsite Exam Centre. Good luck!
* '''Player:''' *sigh*
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Asgarnia Smith again====
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' Good to see you, kid. Did you speak to Terry Balando?
* '''Player:''' You know I still haven't agreed to help you, right?
* '''Asgarnia Smith:''' You'll find Terry at the Digsite Exam Centre. You'd best get going. There's treasure to uncover!
* '''Player:''' *sigh*
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Terry Balando===
* '''Terry Balando:''' Hello again. How goes the archaeology?
* '''Player:''' Pretty good, thanks. In fact, I've come across something I was hoping you could help me with.
* '''Terry Balando:''' What is it?
* '''Player:''' I came across something very interesting down in the desert: A Zarosian vault.
* '''Terry Balando:''' Zarosian? Like that artefact you found for us?
* '''Player:''' Exactly! I'm hoping to learn about four names I discovered on statues within the vault.
* '''Terry Balando:''' Sounds like an exciting discovery, but I'm afraid I can't help. This 'Zaros' is still mostly a mystery to me. In fact, I'd say you probably know more than I do!
* '''Player:''' So what would you suggest?
* '''Terry Balando:''' Well you may well be in luck. We had a new arrival at the Digsite recently who claims to be a Zarosian expert!
* '''Terry Balando:''' Quite impressive for one of those to exist considering the greatest historians and archaeologists in the world has no knowledge on Zaros until very recently...
* '''Player:''' Interesting... Where can I find this expert?
* '''Terry Balando:''' He's set up a new dig on the eastern edge of the Digsite. You're looking for... Ah, what was his name again...
* '''Terry Balando:''' Nabanik? No, that's not right...
* '''Terry Balando:''' Banikan! You'll be wanting to speak to Dr Banikan!
* '''Player:''' Great! I'll head over there and see if I can find him.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Terry Balando again====
* '''Terry Balando:''' Hello again. Did you speak to Dr Banikan?
* '''Player:''' Not yet.
* '''Terry Balando:''' He's set up a new dig on the eastern edge of the Digsite. You'll likely find him there.
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Terry Balando again after talking to Dr Banikan====
* '''Terry Balando:''' Hello again. How goes the archaeology?
* '''Player:''' Pretty good, thanks.
* '''Terry Balando:''' Glad to hear it!
* {{tact|end}}

===Attempting to visit the new dig before speaking to Terry Balando===
* {{tbox|You haven't been given permission to use that.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to Dr Banikan===
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Oh... Good day, adventurer.
* '''Player:''' Dr Banikan, I presume?
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Banikan? Yes... I am Banikan.
* '''Player:''' Are you sure? You don't seem very sure...
* '''Dr Banikan:''' My apologies. I was not expecting company down here, so you caught me a bit off guard.
* '''Player:''' Hmm... We haven't met before, have we? You seem familiar.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' I don't believe so.
* '''Player:''' Hmm... Fair enough.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' So tell me, adventurer, what brings you down here?
* '''Player:''' I've been told you're a Zarosian expert. I was hoping you could help me with some names.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Names? What names?
* '''Player:''' Vardorvis, Perseriya, Duke Sucellus and the Whisperer. I believe they were all Zarosians.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' ...
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Where did you hear these names?
* '''Player:''' I found a strange vault down in the desert, on the eastern coast. The names were on four statues inside.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' A Zarosian vault? How curious...
* '''Player:''' So can you help?
* '''Dr Banikan:''' I think so. I suspect the information you seek can be found in the very place I'm searching for.
* '''Player:''' Excellent! Where's that?
* '''Dr Banikan:''' You seem to be fairly knowledgeable when it comes to the Zarosian Empire, which is quite a rarity these days. How much do you know about its fall?
* '''Player:''' I know that Zaros was overthrown by one of his most trusted generals, Zamorak, who became a god as a result.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Spot on! You could teach the so-called experts around here a thing or two. The betrayal of Zaros ultimately led to the God Wars, making it quite possibly the most pivotal moment in all of history.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' However, even to those of us who do know our stuff, much of what happened to the empire following Zaros' defeat is still a mystery. That's why I'm here.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Senntisten, the Zarosian settlement once located here, was believed to be the capital of the empire.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' If my research is right, and I have strong reason to believe it is, the remains of a key military installation are located right beneath us.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' I can definitely think of worse places to discover details on the fall of the empire.
* '''Player:''' And you think this military installation could have information on the four names I found?
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Absolutely! Any respectable military outpost would have been filled to the brim with key strategic intelligence. I'd expect details on notable Zarosians to be included.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Of course, they wouldn't have wanted that information falling into the wrong hands, so recovering it may not be straightforward...
* '''Player:''' Well I do love a good challenge.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Glad to hear it. Now, I have made good progress in excavating these ruins so far, but perhaps you can help me with the final step?
* '''Player:''' Sounds like something I'd be good at! What do you need me to blow up?
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Excuse me?
* '''Player:''' Well, my first major discovery here involved me blowing a big hole in some rocks to access an ancient temple. Shouldn't be too hard to do that again.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' I'm sorry, what?
* '''Player:''' What's the problem?
* '''Dr Banikan:''' You risked the structural integrity of an ancient temple by blowing it open with explosives?!
* '''Player:''' Huh... I guess I never thought about it like that before. Yeah... now that you mention it, that was really quite a stupid idea.
* '''Dr Banikan:''' How about we take just a touch more care with this one?
* '''Player:''' Good idea. What do you need me to do?
* '''Dr Banikan:''' Grab yourself a pickaxe and carefully clear away these rocks. There should be a pickaxe in the crate in the corner.
* '''Player:''' Okay, will do.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|So how come you know so much about Zaros?}}
** '''Player:''' So how come you know so much about Zaros?
** '''Dr Banikan:''' Well... in my travels, I ended up spending a great deal of time in one of the few places Zarosian remnants can still be found. My time studying them filled me with fascination, and sadness.
** '''Player:''' Sadness?
** '''Dr Banikan:''' 'I walked across the sands and saw the ruins of time...'
** '''Player:''' What?
** '''Dr Banikan:''' It's an old poem about the rise, and inevitable fall, of kingdoms and empires. Once, Zaros' Empire stretched as far as the eye could see. Now, no one even remembers his name.
** '''Dr Banikan:''' To think that something that was once so absolute may soon be lost forever... It falls to people like me, and perhaps you as well, to ensure that history isn't forgotten.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|What is it you're searching for here?}}
** '''Player:''' What is it you're searching for here?
** '''Dr Banikan:''' As I said, I hope to find details about the fall of the Zarosian Empire.
** '''Player:''' Anything in particular though?
** '''Dr Banikan:''' I have a few leads. Details on individuals and artefacts that may have played a key role in the final days of the Empire.
** '''Player:''' Do you think my four names could be connected?
** '''Dr Banikan:''' I'd say it's definitely possible. I suppose there's only one way to find out.
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|I'd best get to work.}}
** '''Player:''' I'd best get to work.
** {{tact|end}}

