===Talking to Kasonde back on the surface===
* '''Kasonde:''' That was too close. You nearly got us both killed!
* '''Player:''' I don't understand... What are those things? Are they zombies?
* '''Kasonde:''' You really want me to believe that you don't know anything about this place?
* '''Player:''' I already told you, I wasn't lying.
* '''Kasonde:''' Well I don't have any reason to trust that.
* '''Player:''' With how dangerous this place is, do you really have a choice?
* '''Kasonde:''' Hmm...
* '''Kasonde:''' Alright, fine. But I have no desire to see you get us killed, so you'd better wisen up fast.
* '''Player:''' I'm listening.
* '''Kasonde:''' It all starts with the Old Ones. They lived here long before humans came to these lands, and these ruins here were once their home.
* '''Player:''' And these Old Ones discovered soul transference?
* '''Kasonde:''' They did, and they did so long before House Arceuus even existed. It was their final attempt to overcome their extinction, but they failed.
* '''Kasonde:''' What you see around you is the result of their failure. It's known as the Strangler.
* '''Player:''' The Strangler?
* '''Kasonde:''' It's some sort of parasite. It was presumably meant to play a role in their transference rituals, but instead it destroyed them. It has remained here ever since.
* '''Player:''' Hence the Strangled?
* '''Kasonde:''' Exactly. Plenty of unwary fools have fallen victim to the Strangler. If you don't take care, you will share their fate.
* '''Player:''' So how do we deal with them?
* '''Kasonde:''' The trick is to maintain your distance. They're relatively passive unless you get too close, but if you disturb one, the rest will quickly come running.
* '''Kasonde:''' If you need to fight one, try to do it away from the rest!
* '''Kasonde:''' And stay off of the tendrils! You'll alert the lot of them to your location! It's like a network.
* '''Player:''' Keep my distance and stay off the tendrils. I can do that. So what's our next move?
* '''Kasonde:''' The fact that you're still alive tells me you broke into my home and stole some of the potion I made.
* '''Player:''' 'Broke in' is maybe a bit strong...
* '''Kasonde:''' Call it what you want, it's not important now. What is important is that I believe I can make a more powerful potion using ingredients found here.
* '''Kasonde:''' If all goes well, this potion will provide increased immunity against the Strangler. If either of us are to find what we want here, it will be essential.
* '''Player:''' So what ingredients do we need?
* '''Kasonde:''' As you've no doubt seen, the Strangler infects plant life as well. However, I've come across a small number of plants that seem to have developed immunity.
* '''Kasonde:''' First, there's a herb growing atop the cliff just north west of the temple. Second, there are some berries in an old camp on the coast to the south west.
* '''Player:''' Alright, I can gather those.
* '''Kasonde:''' I need to gather some additional ingredients from within the temple. I will meet you back here once I'm done.
* {{tact|end}}

