* '''Hazeel:''' We have failed.
* '''Enakhra:''' Hmph!
* '''Enakhra:''' I'll see you at the ritual, Akthanakos. Perhaps this one will be your last.
* {{qact|Enakhra teleports away.}}
* '''Akthanakos:''' Our allies must be informed of this. Come, Azzanadra.
* {{qact|Akthanakos teleports away, and the cutscene ends.}}
* '''Hazeel:''' It seems your pet has broken free of his leash, Azzanadra.
* '''Azzanadra:''' You know as much as I that Sliske serves no one but himself. His actions are his own.
* '''Hazeel:''' Yet you have shielded him for centuries. A choice that all of us may now suffer from.
* '''Azzanadra:''' You can blame me as much as you wish, Hazeel. It is irrelevant. Sliske now holds the Elder Horn and we must be ready to oppose him.
* '''Hazeel:''' We? You made your choice a long time ago, Azzanadra. There is no 'we' anymore.
* '''Azzanadra:''' And yet you yourself admit that Sliske poses a threat to us all. The prospect of working with Zamorakians gives me no pleasure, but it may be the only option.
* '''Hazeel:''' Perhaps. Perhaps not. Time will soon tell.
* '''Hazeel:''' Now, we're done here. I'll see you soon, Azzanadra.
* {{qact|Hazeel teleports away.}}
* '''Azzanadra:''' Well, adventurer, it seems I owe you an apology.
* '''Player:''' You do?
* '''Azzanadra:''' I did not show you the trust that you deserved. You freed me from my prison, a feat even my closest followers failed to achieve, and yet I doubted you.
* '''Azzanadra:''' I did not know your allegiance, and so I was cautious, but it is clear that focusing on allegiances has blinded us. Sliske took advantage of that.
* '''Player:''' Oh, well thank you, I suppose.
* '''Azzanadra:''' Now, I must ask about the destruction of the Frostenhorn. Sliske's doing?
* '''Player:''' It must have been.
* '''Azzanadra:''' Then I fear the other artefacts will have met a similar fate.
* '''Player:''' Other artefacts?
* '''Azzanadra:''' The Frostenhorn was one of three powerful items I was seeking. Together, they may have been my best chance to determine the fate of my lord.
* '''Player:''' And Sliske didn't want that?
* '''Azzanadra:''' Apparently not, though who could say why. I would never describe Sliske as a true believer, but until now, he always supported the Empty Lord.
* '''Azzanadra:''' Indeed, he himself was entrusted with another of the three artefacts. An icon that was kept under close guard by those wights of his.
* '''Player:''' Ah... Well unless they were guarding multiple icons, I'm afraid Sliske destroyed that one as well. As for your third artefact, it didn't happen to be on Entrana, did it?
* '''Azzanadra:''' I had yet to track it down, but that does seem likely. It was stolen by Saradominists long ago.
* '''Player:''' Then I think it's safe to say it's been destroyed too. Sliske stole it from Entrana while disguised as that assassin.
* '''Azzanadra:''' So my worst fears are confirmed. This may well be the darkest day for us since the fall of the Empty Lord.
* '''Player:''' What will you do now?
* '''Azzanadra:''' Since you freed me, I have been driven by a singular purpose. I exist for Zaros. I exist for the Empire. Sliske thinks he has destroyed that purpose, but I will not give up.
* '''Azzanadra:''' However, that is for another day. There are more immediate matters to concern myself with now. The Ritual of the Mahjarrat is fast approaching, and whatever Sliske is planning will happen there.
* '''Azzanadra:''' I must ensure I am prepared, and while it may not have been your intention, you are part of this now. You must also ensure you are ready. To help with this, I have something to offer you.
* '''Azzanadra:''' I understand you are in possession of a ring that lets you see into the Shadow Realm? Considering Sliske's mastery over that place, that is a power that will likely be of great use to you.
* '''Azzanadra:''' Allow me to upgrade it with some offensive and defensive enchantments. They may well give you an important edge if you find yourself fighting in the shadows.
* {{tcond|If the player did not bring their ring of visibility:}}
** '''Player:''' Thank you. Do you need me to fetch the ring for you?
** '''Azzanadra:''' No need. I can summon it with ease.
** {{tact|continue}}
* {{tcond|If the player brought their ring of visibility:}}
** '''Player:''' Thank you.
** {{tact|continue}}
* '''Azzanadra:''' And on that note, I must leave you, my friend. May you walk in the shadow of the Empty Lord.
* {{tact|end}}
{{qact|Congratulations! Quest complete!}}

